  m_Name: Chess
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::CodexEntry
  title: Chess
  description: 'Chess was a widely respected board game among the upper classes during
    the 18th and 19th centuries. It was commonly played in parlors and drawing rooms
    as both entertainment and a demonstration of strategic thinking and education.
    In wealthy households, chess sets were often decorative as well as functional,
    reflecting the status of the owner. '
